FBIS3-249 "drafr043_b_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia Former Italian Embassy Comes Under Fire LD0403113094 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1045 GMT 4 Mar 94 LD0403113094 Rome RAI Due Television Network Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] We have just heard that for about half an hour this morning about 20 Somalis directed fire at the former Italian Embassy in Mogadishu, in which a unit of the Italian contingent is based. Guards returned fire, as did the crews on two caterpillar vehicles that were returning to the base when they also came under attack. No Italians have been hurt. The Somalis fled shortly afterward and it is not known if any of them were hurt. The motives behind the attack are not yet known.
